## Recommended Azure Resources

### Application: Mathematically Correct Builds (main-app)
- **Hosting Service Type**: Azure Container Apps
- **SKU**: Consumption tier (pay per use, auto-scale)
- **Configuration**:
  - **Language**: Python 3.14
  - **Framework**: Flask 3.0+
  - **Port**: 5000 (exposed via ingress)
  - **Environment Variables**:
    - `FLASK_ENV=production`
    - `FLASK_APP=main.py`
    - `PORT=5000`
  - **Docker Image**: Stored in Azure Container Registry
  - **Memory**: 0.5-4 Gi (starts at 0.5, auto-scales)
  - **CPU**: 0.25-2 (starts at 0.25, auto-scales)
  
- **Dependencies**: None (self-contained, local JSON caching)

### Supporting Services

#### Azure Container Registry (ACR)
- **SKU**: Basic (sufficient for small apps)
- **Purpose**: Store and manage Flask application Docker images
- **Registry Name**: acrMathematicallyCorrectBuilds{uniqueString}

#### Log Analytics Workspace
- **SKU**: Pay-as-you-go
- **Purpose**: Centralized logging and monitoring for Container Apps
- **Ingestion Tier**: 100GB/day included

#### Application Insights
- **SKU**: Basic
- **Purpose**: Application performance monitoring and diagnostics
- **Connected to**: Log Analytics Workspace

#### User-Assigned Managed Identity
- **Purpose**: 
  - Container App authentication to ACR (AcrPull role)
  - GitHub Actions OIDC authentication to Azure
- **Role Assignments**:
  - AcrPull (7f951dda-4ed3-4680-a7ca-43fe172d538d) on ACR
  - Contributor on resource group (for GitHub Actions deployment)

## Security Configurations

- ✅ User-Assigned Managed Identity attached to Container App (NOT system identity)
- ✅ AcrPull role assignment for ACR access
- ✅ GitHub Actions OIDC federation for passwordless authentication
- ✅ Container App ingress CORS enabled for cross-origin requests
- ✅ Application logs sent to Log Analytics Workspace
- ✅ No hardcoded secrets; all config from environment variables

## Execution Steps

### 1. Containerization
- [ ] Ensure Docker is installed and running
- [ ] Generate Dockerfile using appmod-plan-generate-dockerfile
- [ ] Build Docker image locally for validation
- [ ] **Output**: Dockerfile in project root

### 2. Azure CLI Setup
- [ ] Install Azure CLI (if not present)
- [ ] Run `az login` to authenticate
- [ ] Set default subscription: `az account set --subscription <subscription-id>`
- [ ] Verify setup: `az account show`

### 3. Provision Azure Infrastructure with Bicep
- [ ] Generate Bicep files in infra/ folder:
  - main.bicep
  - main.parameters.json
- [ ] Validate Bicep syntax: `az bicep build --file infra/main.bicep`
- [ ] Create resource group: `az group create --name mcb-prod --location eastus`
- [ ] Deploy infrastructure:
  ```powershell
  az deployment group create `
    --name mcb-deploy `
    --resource-group mcb-prod `
    --template-file infra/main.bicep `
    --parameters infra/main.parameters.json
  ```
- [ ] Capture ACR login server and resource IDs from deployment output

### 4. Build and Push Docker Image
- [ ] Authenticate with ACR: `az acr login --name acrMcb...`
- [ ] Build image: `docker build -t app:latest .`
- [ ] Tag for ACR: `docker tag app:latest acrMcb....azurecr.io/app:latest`
- [ ] Push to ACR: `docker push acrMcb....azurecr.io/app:latest`
- [ ] **Output**: Docker image in ACR

### 5. Deploy to Azure Container Apps
- [ ] Create deployment script to update Container App with new image
- [ ] Run deployment script
- [ ] Verify deployment: `az containerapp show --resource-group mcb-prod --name app`
- [ ] Get Container App URL from ingress property
- [ ] **Output**: Live application URL

### 6. Configure GitHub Actions CI/CD
- [ ] Create user-assigned managed identity for GitHub Actions (separate from app identity)
- [ ] Set up OIDC federated credentials:
  - Subject: `repo:{owner}/{repo}:environment:production`
  - Issuer: `https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com`
- [ ] Create GitHub environments (dev, staging, production)
- [ ] Configure branch protection rules
- [ ] Set GitHub Actions secrets:
  - `AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID`
  - `AZURE_CLIENT_ID`
  - `AZURE_TENANT_ID`
  - `AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP`
  - `REGISTRY_LOGIN_SERVER`
  - `REGISTRY_NAME`
- [ ] Generate GitHub Actions workflow files:
  - `.github/workflows/build-test.yml` (CI: build and test on PR)
  - `.github/workflows/deploy-dev.yml` (CD: deploy to dev on main)
  - `.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml` (CD: deploy to production with approval)
  - `.github/workflows/infra-deploy.yml` (Infrastructure provisioning)

### 7. Final Validation
- [ ] Test GitHub Actions workflows with sample commits
- [ ] Verify application logs in Log Analytics
- [ ] Check Application Insights for performance metrics
- [ ] Test application endpoints
- [ ] Summarize deployment with appmod-summarize-result

## Progress Tracking

Progress will be updated in `.azure/progress.copilotmd` after each major step:
- ✅ = Complete
- 🔄 = In Progress
- ⏳ = Pending
- ❌ = Failed (with error notes)

